  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Hard prompt methods remove unnecessary tokens from the original prompt while maintaining the use of natural language words or sub-words (Reynolds and McDonell, 2021).",
    "These methods are particularly useful for LLMs that only accept natural language inputs, such as close API models, rather than word embeddings.",
    "There are three representative hard prompt methods: SelectiveContext (Li et al., 2023) and LLMLingua (Jiang et al., 2023) for filtering, and Nano-Capsulator (Chuang et al., 2024) for paraphrasing, as shown in Figure 3.",
    "SelectiveContext identifies and deletes redundant or less informative parts of an input prompt by quantifying the informativeness of lexical units using self-information (Li et al., 2023).",
    "To maintain text coherence, the syntactic parsing capabilities of SpaCy foot_1 are used to group individual tokens into noun phrases based on dependency parsing."
  ],
